About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

Details:
Synergy focuses on training individuals on project management concepts and software tools such as Microsoft Office Project, MSP Server, Primavera, and Primavera Complete, Asta Power Project. The courses will be offered in 70 locations across India and in 7 countries, as listed in its website. 
Synergy also trains on PMP Certification Preparatory module, and conducts PME (Project Management Expert) Certification for PM Aspirants. 
The training outcome with Project Management Skills include: Realistic Budgeting, Resource Estimation, Testing Methods, Better Communication, and Effective Risk Management that keep the pace of production high, both qualitatively and quantitatively. Synergy enrolls Students and Professionals of Management and Engineering specialization viz., Mechanical, Civil, Electrical, Electronics, Instrumentation, Business Administration & IT
Synergy offers training on Tally software, MS Office and Placement Training through its course called Master Diploma in Business Automation. 
The School will also help students find employment in the relevant corporate firms for the respective programs.

Details:
Elysium Group of Companies (EGC) is initiated in 1999 at Singapore and managed to emerge as one of the largest global solutions firm in Asia and a leading provider of information technology and business process outsourcing services to build stronger businesses. Currently, our Elysium Groups have established 12 domestic branches across India and serves 1031 Global Clients across 21 Countries. With 16 years of proficiency and expertise in the field of IT sector, we have initiated our footstep in futuristic technical education sector to nurture the inherent potential and talent of each aspiring learner and create the lifelong aspirants and innovative global citizens with a strong sense of values. Elysium Groups initiated the Elysium Academy Private Limited (EAPL) with a vision of being the leading center of learning and innovation in the emerging areas of the knowledge society. 
Our corporate philosophy of staying ahead in providing the latest IT technologies and a quality learning experience, have motivated us to emerge as a major force in IT education in India. Our core areas of specialism include networking, software, voice and security. Our academy currently focuses on providing advanced training and certifications in the specialized areas, according to the global standards. Our academy offers a comprehensive collection of certification courses from REDHAT, CISCO, MICROSOFT, CEH, COMPTIA and VMware with highly qualified and experienced certified professionals. Our portfolio of technology-based education solutions and structure blended training programs promised us a consistent reach to the enthusiastic learners. Practical training session serves as a gateway of providing excellent training & real-world experience to the learners.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

Details:
Elysium Group of Companies (EGC) is initiated in 1999 at Singapore and managed to emerge as one of the largest global solutions firm in Asia and a leading provider of information technology and business process outsourcing services to build stronger businesses. Currently, our Elysium Groups have established 12 domestic branches across India and serves 1031 Global Clients across 21 Countries. With 16 years of proficiency and expertise in the field of IT sector, we have initiated our footstep in futuristic technical education sector to nurture the inherent potential and talent of each aspiring learner and create the lifelong aspirants and innovative global citizens with a strong sense of values. Elysium Groups initiated the Elysium Academy Private Limited (EAPL) with a vision of being the leading center of learning and innovation in the emerging areas of the knowledge society. 
Our corporate philosophy of staying ahead in providing the latest IT technologies and a quality learning experience, have motivated us to emerge as a major force in IT education in India. Our core areas of specialism include networking, software, voice and security. Our academy currently focuses on providing advanced training and certifications in the specialized areas, according to the global standards. Our academy offers a comprehensive collection of certification courses from REDHAT, CISCO, MICROSOFT, CEH, COMPTIA and VMware with highly qualified and experienced certified professionals. Our portfolio of technology-based education solutions and structure blended training programs promised us a consistent reach to the enthusiastic learners. Practical training session serves as a gateway of providing excellent training & real-world experience to the learners.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

Institutes For Game DesigningPlacement @ Image
The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.

About Image:
We offer fully practice -oriented design and media courses with 100% placement assurance. Our expert faculties provide individual guidance to help you groom as an industry-ready, trained professional.
Partnered with National Skill Development Council
IMAGE Creative Education has partnered with National Skill Development Council (NSDC), an initiative taken by the Government of India to offer skill improvement training to millions of young minds across India. As NSDC has joined hands with various organizations to render training services in different sectors, IMAGE Creative Education has been selected to provide training under the Media and Entertainment sector.
With this alliance, IMAGE Creative Education will offer training services to more than 1 Lakh youth in a span of 10 years. IMAGE will implement its services through its network of training centres across India.
The students of IMAGE undertaking any vocational/skill development courses, be it short term or long term, will now be eligible to avail educational loans from various nationalized banks. This alliance with NSDC will also open up more avenues for job placement.

The Placement Department of IMAGE Creative Education works closely with the institutions training and research wing and industry professionals to bridge the gap between the academia and the industry. The Placement Department continuously strives to understand the current requirements of the industry and expose the students to the latest trends. It provides a platform for the students to interact with the industry professionals, which would aid potential employers to engage with our talent pool. The Placement Department also provides assistance to the alumni of the institution.
The vision of our Placement Department is To place each student in the right company, in the right position, with the best package, that best suits the skills of the student.
With over two decades of experience in training skilled professionals, IMAGE Creative Education stands at its best in addressing the trending needs of the employers.
The Placement team works closely with companies in the Design and Media industry to identify their skilled-talent requirements. Once the team gets to know about an opportunity, it seeks clear requirements, shortlists profiles, sends profiles to employers and arranges interview for shortlisted students.
In case of mass recruitment drives, the Placement department trains the students on specific employer needs, before sending the students to the interview. This is also done as a service to organizations that continuously recruit our students year-on-year. So far, the Placement department has been highly successful in placing its students in top-notch companies around the world.
